The European Investment Bank (EIB) Group will provide Û1.7 billion to support the social and economic recovery of the Western Balkans from the COVID-19 pandemic. A) An immediate fast-track action for a total of some EUR 450m aimed at accelerating existing operations in order to support urgent health-related measures and sustain the survival of enterprises and jobs in sectors most affected by the impact of the coronavirus;
 B) A new EUR 500m Regional Facility which will address urgent needs in the public sector including the health care systems and other activities directly linked to the outbreak of the disease. The Facility can also be used by the public sector bodies to support the economic recovery, with a particular emphasis on SMEs;
 C) A new EUR 400m Regional Financing Facility to be delivered through a number of financial institutions (banks, leasing companies and any other qualifying financial institutions) will reach out to as many companies as possible. The purpose of the facility is to support immediate liquidity needs and address investment constraints of SMEs and Midcaps, which are most affected by the COVID-19 outbreak.
 D) EUR 350m of our existing pipeline of projects to be financed in the coming years throughout the Region. These projects are at various stages of preparation and are in line with the EC priorities in the Region. Particular attention will be paid to the healthcare sector in keeping with pre-crisis priorities.
